rom the welfare state. In this much-needed text by an experienced author with a policy background, current housing finance issues (and their history) are linked with broader social policy and political themes. It covers the finance of building and refurbishment, managing and maintaining property for all the different tenures (owner occupation, council housing, housing association and private renting), and discusses whether current arrangements are sustainable. Written for housing, social policy and politics students and staff, it is also accessible to anyone concerned about housing in Britain today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHousing policyzGreat Britain. 0aHousingzGreat BritainxFinance. 0aPublic housingzGreat BritainxFinance. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730648140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447316572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447316572/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013